HEADWORD: Hest
<hw>Hest</hw> <pr>(h⟦ecr⟧st)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>h⟦aemac⟧s</ets>, fr. <ets>h⟦amac⟧tan</ets> to call, bid. See
<er>Hight</er>, and cf. <er>Behest</er>.]</ety> <def>Command; precept;
injunction.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark> <see>See <er>Behest</er>.</see>
⟦ldquo⟧At thy <xex>hest</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let him that yields obey the victor's <qex>hest</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Fairfax.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Yet I thy <qex>hest</qex> will all perform, at full.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj></p>

<p><ent>Hesternal</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Hestern</ent>⟦br⟧
